  "title": "Landscape Manager",
  "description": "<p>Job Description </p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· Attend site visits and tender show round</p>\n<p>· Propose and design simple yet sustainable landscape designs for specified sites</p>\n<p>· Prepare quotes and landscape maintenance reports</p>\n<p>· Coordinate work orders with ground crew</p>\n<p>· Dealing with complaints from client on site</p>\n<p>· Prepare maintenance schedule</p>\n<p>· Monitor and recording of site staff attendance</p>\n<p>· Handling few projects assigned and coordination</p>\n<p>· To be responsible for the administrative and operational for landscape project aspects, including liaise with customers for project requirements and progress</p>\n<p>· Facilitate on the job training program for new crew members and provide ongoing training for crew members’ skill development objectives</p>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<p>· Degree/Diploma in Horticulture, Arboriculture or other related fields with minimum of 1 yr experience in landscaping industries</p>\n<p>· Required language(s): English, Chinese (in order to deal with complaints from Chinese speaking client on site)</p>\n<p>· Dynamic and energetic</p>\n<p>· Good team player with ability to lead and multi-task</p>\n<p>· Committed to work</p>\n<p>· Required Skill(s): Microsoft Office</p>\n<p>· Excellent interpersonal and communication skills</p>\n<p>· Prefer candidates with horticulture or arborist knowledge</p>\n<p>· On-the-job training provided</p>\n<p>· Entry level candidates with the relevant Polytechnic / WSQ Diploma / Degree are welcomed</p>\n<p>Working Hours and Office Location:</p>\n<p>· 5.5-day work week</p>\n<p>· Office location: Mandai Estate</p>\n<p>· Work location: Various Sites</p>",
